      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add truncation-risk ClawScan rescan mode",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR adds an operator rescan mode for active latest skills that are large enough to be affected by prompt truncation boundaries.\n\n## Scenario this protects\n\nIf maintainers change scanner rules, adjust prompt limits, or identify a class of artifacts that needs fresh review, they need a focused way to queue rescans. Without that, the choices are either manual one-by-one rescans or a broad rescan of every active skill.\n\nThis PR adds the narrower path for the truncation-risk case.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Adds `truncation-risk-latest` to the admin bulk ClawScan rescan API.\n- Adds the same mode to `clawhub-admin skills rescan-all`.\n- Supports dry-run output so operators can count and sample the affected set before creating jobs.\n- Queues fresh ClawScan jobs only for active latest skills whose primary `SKILL.md` or `skills.md` is large enough to deserve another look.\n- Updates public/operator docs and the security moderation spec to describe scan results as current risk signals, not permanent certification.\n\n## Operator flow\n\nFirst inspect scope:\n\n```sh\nbun run admin -- skills rescan-all --mode truncation-risk-latest --dry-run --json\n```\n\nThen queue jobs when the scope looks right:\n\n```sh\nbun run admin -- skills rescan-all --mode truncation-risk-latest --yes\n```\n\n## What this does not change\n\nThis does not change scanner verdict logic, install gating, hide/unhide behavior, or manual moderation decisions. It only adds a targeted way to refresh existing published artifacts.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n- `bun test packages/clawhub-admin/src/commands/moderation.test.ts`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/vitest run convex/securityScan.test.ts`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/vitest run packages/schema/src/schemas.test.ts`\n- `bun run --cwd packages/schema build`\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/schema/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/clawhub/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n- `bun run --cwd packages/clawhub-admin typecheck`\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base upstream/main --reviewer copilot --fallback-reviewer none --parallel-tests \"\"`\n",
        "branch": "brzezowski/ops-rescan-truncation-risk",
